76561198074867492,Recommended,320540,25344110,"Posted: 4 September, 2016",all,Dragon Force,"TitleCoffin DodgersDeveloperMilky Tea StudiosPublisherWales InteractiveRelease8 July 2015Graphics3DGenreRacingPrice€9,99Rating6.5/10The game.Coffin Dodgersis a fun and little cartoonish kart racing game, running around with old people in mobility scooters where the last runners are being caught by Reaper and then they run like zombies.Gameplay.The game consists of 13 race tracks spread over 4 different areas and you can play as one of the 8 playable characters. Each character have different ""powers"", but the difference between each one is very small, that seems only visual.The controls could be better, are simple (but sometimes sounds a little stiff), gameplay is simple, fun and addictive. During the game, you have the challenge of improving your vehicle with very funny visual upgrades. It has a lot of playable mods from single to multiplayer, which allows a wide range of choice. Open-world explore is a good and interesting mode to play. However, the multiplayer seems be nonexistent. Short game but very fun. While I played, I had a lot of fun.A note for the tutorial, simple and useful. New players will not have problems to start playing. At last, I don't understand the negative reviews that I read on the game page on Steam about this game. Seriously.Recommended game to buy on sale (as I did).Positive points. (+)Original and super fun concept.Useful tutorial.Fun gameplay.Controls could be better, but they're decent and nice to play.Pretty decent variety of weapons, upgrades and playable mods.Quite good for playing in family/with friends.Really interesting graphic models and textures, reminding cartoon.Negative points. (-)Controls aren't bad, but sometimes seemed a little stiff.Uninspired music.Multiplayer is nonexistent."
